products.name: Elvang Basket throw Beige
products.description:
The Basket throw is inspired by a beautifully woven basket characterized by its vivid structure. If you love a big and chunky throw to keep you warm with your favourite book and a cup of coffee, Basket is an obvious contender. An elegant and timeless design.The Basket throw is woven from 100% recycled materials.The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 35% alpaca wool, 35% sheep wool & 30% andre fiber
Weight: app. 970 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inchesWe recommend
Care: Dry clean only

products.description:
The Manhattan cushion is inspired by the way the straight streets and right angles create square blocks in New York’s borough of Manhattan. Lines crisscross and create contrast and vibrancy. The design creates a balance between the classic, timeless and forward-thinking modern look.The Manhattan cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber

Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang *SALE* Star Duvet220x220cm White
products.description:
The duvet cover has a functional zipper closure and the pillow case an envelope closure with a beautiful small hem. The combination of cotton and linen makes the bed linen more environmentally friendly, durable and breathable. The prewashed garment offers a perfect fit and a soft, casual look – no need to iron. It will keep you snug in winter and cool during the summer. Combined with our beautiful Bellis cushion collection in three different sizes together with our Daisy bedcover you will have that perfect hotel feel in your bedroom.The responsible production of our organic cotton and linen collections takes place in Portugal at a GOTS certified factory. GOTS is short for Global Organic Textile Standard. This is your guarantee that the products are made according to the environmentally and socially responsible standards. Furthermore, we comply with the STANDARD 100 by OEKO-TEX® ensuring that our collections are free from any harmful substances.ELVANG is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed member.

Material: 70% organic cotton and 30% linen (GOTS certified)
Size: 140x200 cm / 55x71 inchesWashable at 40 degrees

products.name: Elvang *SPECIAL OFFER* Dahlia Throw Light Grey
products.description:
The collection is beautifully crafted and with the combination of linen the throw exudes a touch of rawness and offers an amazing structure. products.name: Elvang Daisy Bedcover Camel
products.description:
Our Daisy bedcover collection is naturally smooth and have a soft and aesthetic appeal and will add a mild and cosy feel to your bedroom. The design is calm and understated - yet the short eyelash fringes with one colour represented on each side add a distinguished touch. The bedcover looks beautiful in combination with our STAR bed linen also woven in organic cotton and linen. If our Bellis cushions are added you will have a hotel feel in your bedroom. The responsible production of our organic cotton and linen collections takes place in Portugal at a GOTS certified factory. GOTS is short for Global Organic Textile Standard. This is your guarantee that the products are made according to the environmentally and socially responsible standards. Furthermore, we comply with the STANDARD 100 by OEKO-TEX® ensuring that our collections are free from any harmful substances.ELVANG is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed member.

Material: 80% organic cotton and 20% linen (GOTS certified)
Weight: approx. 1000g
Size: 240x220 cm / 94x87 inches

products.description:
The Classic cushion is beautiful simplicity, and the collection comes in a range of classic colours that never go out of style. An uncomplicated and minimalistic cushion design – a true classic in every home.The Classic cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Amsterdam scarf Dark blue
products.description:
The amazing weaving technique makes the scarf artful and elegant, and the beautiful intervening of the playful stripes elevates the classic design expression. The luxurious scarf comes in camel, dark blue and grey and is the perfect versatile accessory to elevate your look. Amsterdam is finished with fine light fringes in the colours of the scarf. The scarf is made from the amazingly soft sustainable baby alpaca wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the scarf will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The scarf is made of pure sustainable baby alpaca wool. This is the finest alpaca wool and it can´t get any better than that. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the scarf is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 100% baby alpaca wool
Weight: app. 225 g
Size: 50x196 cm / 20x77 inchesCan be washed at wool programme at 30 degrees
Care: Machine washable

products.description:
The Basket throw is inspired by a beautifully woven basket characterized by its vivid structure. If you love a big and chunky throw to keep you warm with your favourite book and a cup of coffee, Basket is an obvious contender. An elegant and timeless design.The Basket throw is woven from 100% recycled materials.The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 35% alpaca wool, 35% sheep wool & 30% andre fiber

Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inchesWe recommend
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Horizon throw Camel
products.description:
The Horizon throw is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The throw is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching cushions in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your throw does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inche
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Horizon cushion 40x60cm Camel
products.description:
The Horizon cushion is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The cushion is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching throws in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your cushion does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.description:
The Classic cushion is beautiful simplicity, and the collection comes in a range of classic colours that never go out of style. An uncomplicated and minimalistic cushion design – a true classic in every home.The Classic cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Horizon cushion 40x60cm Rusty red
products.description:
The Horizon cushion is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The cushion is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching throws in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your cushion does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Basket throw Nude
products.description:
The Basket throw is inspired by a beautifully woven basket characterized by its vivid structure. If you love a big and chunky throw to keep you warm with your favourite book and a cup of coffee, Basket is an obvious contender. An elegant and timeless design.The Basket throw is woven from 100% recycled materials.The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 35% alpaca wool, 35% sheep wool & 30% andre fiber
Weight: app. 970 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inchesWe recommend
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Stripes throw Green
products.description:
The Stripes throw collection is uncomplicated and dynamic with a classic touch. The fine ongoing lines finalized with decorative eyelash fringes makes Stripes a timeless and homely companion. Stripes is woven in soft recycled alpaca wool and comes in five beautiful colours. A throw that never goes out of style. The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% andre fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Stripes throw Grey
products.description:
The Stripes throw collection is uncomplicated and dynamic with a classic touch. The fine ongoing lines finalized with decorative eyelash fringes makes Stripes a timeless and homely companion. Stripes is woven in soft recycled alpaca wool and comes in five beautiful colours. A throw that never goes out of style. The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% andre fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Stripes throw Light yellow
products.description:
The Stripes throw collection is uncomplicated and dynamic with a classic touch. The fine ongoing lines finalized with decorative eyelash fringes makes Stripes a timeless and homely companion. Stripes is woven in soft recycled alpaca wool and comes in five beautiful colours. A throw that never goes out of style. The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% andre fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang *SALE* Tweed throw Grey
products.description:
Our Tweed throw is a testament to natural materials meeting pure craftmanship and classic design. The calm pattern with its fine lines is complemented with long and multi-coloured beautiful fringes. Tweed will add that cosy warm feeling of hygge and relaxation to any sofa or chair, while adding a touch of elegancy to the setting. The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fibre
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.description:
Our Tweed throw is a testament to natural materials meeting pure craftmanship and classic design. The calm pattern with its fine lines is complemented with long and multi-coloured beautiful fringes. Tweed will add that cosy warm feeling of hygge and relaxation to any sofa or chair, while adding a touch of elegancy to the setting. The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fibre
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Manhattan throw Beige
products.description:
The Manhattan throw is inspired by the way the straight streets and right angles create square blocks in New York’s borough of Manhattan. Lines crisscross and create contrast and vibrancy. The design creates a balance between the classic, timeless and forward-thinking modern look.The Manhattan throw is woven from 100% recycled materials.The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inchesWe recommend
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Cable throw Brown/black
products.description:
Our Cable throw collection has a wonderful structure that looks like twisted rope. It comes with a two-coloured knitted look and features a beautiful rib stich. Cable is masculine and cosy like a sweater perfect to snuggle up in. The throw is made from the amazingly soft alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool & 50% sheep wool
Weight: app. 1000 gram
Size: 130x180 cm / 51x71 inchesWe recommend
Care: Dry clean only

products.description:
The Manhattan cushion is inspired by the way the straight streets and right angles create square blocks in New York’s borough of Manhattan. Lines crisscross and create contrast and vibrancy. The design creates a balance between the classic, timeless and forward-thinking modern look.The Manhattan cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

An elegant and timeless design.The Basket throw is woven from 100% recycled materials.The throw is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the throw will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The throw is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Weight: app. 970 gram

products.name: Elvang Horizon throw Grey
products.description:
The Horizon throw is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The throw is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching cushions in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your throw does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inche
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang *SALE* Star pillow50x70cm White
products.description:
The duvet cover has a functional zipper closure and the pillow case an envelope closure with a beautiful small hem. The combination of cotton and linen makes the bed linen more environmentally friendly, durable and breathable. The prewashed garment offers a perfect fit and a soft, casual look – no need to iron. It will keep you snug in winter and cool during the summer. Combined with our beautiful Bellis cushion collection in three different sizes together with our Daisy bedcover you will have that perfect hotel feel in your bedroom.The responsible production of our organic cotton and linen collections takes place in Portugal at a GOTS certified factory. GOTS is short for Global Organic Textile Standard. This is your guarantee that the products are made according to the environmentally and socially responsible standards. ELVANG is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed member.

Material: 70% organic cotton and 30% linen
Size: 50x70 cm / 20x28 inchesWashable at 40 degrees

products.name: Elvang *SPECIAL OFFER* Classic cushion 40x60cm Beige
products.description:
The Classic cushion is beautiful simplicity, and the collection comes in a range of classic colours that never go out of style. An uncomplicated and minimalistic cushion design – a true classic in every home.The Classic cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

Elvang Manhattan cushion 40x60cm Natural
products.description:
The Manhattan cushion is inspired by the way the straight streets and right angles create square blocks in New York’s borough of Manhattan. Lines crisscross and create contrast and vibrancy. The design creates a balance between the classic, timeless and forward-thinking modern look.The Manhattan cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Horizon cushion 40x60cm Grey
products.description:
The Horizon cushion is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The cushion is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching throws in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your cushion does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 40x60 cm / 16x24 inches
Care: Dry clean only

The cushion is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching throws in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your cushion does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 130 gram
Size: 50x50 cm / 20x20 inches
Care: Dry clean only

The Classic cushion is beautiful simplicity, and the collection comes in a range of classic colours that never go out of style. An uncomplicated and minimalistic cushion design – a true classic in every home.The Classic cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

products.name: Elvang Ecru Brown Throw
products.description:
The collection called Écru is designed by Danish Cecilie Manz and consists of three throws. They differ from each other both in the base colour and in the discreet stripes along the edges that vary in both weave and colour, giving each throw its own unique identity. The throws come in three classic basic colours - a soft beige, an off-white and a brown. All are the natural colours of baby alpaca wool, which means that the fibres are not dyed.Écru is made from 100% baby alpaca wool, which is known for its unique properties. The wool is thermoregulatory, meaning it can be up to seven times warmer than sheep's wool when it's cold, while appearing light and cool when temperatures rise. This is because alpaca wool fibres are hollow, and therefore naturally insulating. In addition, alpaca fibres are water-repellent and breathable, and the wool is hypoallergenic as it contains no lanolin, making it suitable for allergy sufferers.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest level by the World Fair Trade Organisation (WFTO). This is your guarantee that the throw is produced under decent conditions - both for the environment and people.

Material: 100% baby alpaca wool
Weight: approx. 600 grams
Size: 130 x 207 cm

products.name: Elvang Horizon Throw Camel
products.description:
The Horizon throw is named after the horizon line in the distance, and its characteristic colour gradient that changes from dark to light is the natural motif. The throw is available in 12 beautiful colour interpretations from a dusty green to a saturated ochre, and can of course be matched with matching cushions in the same pattern and colour scheme for a cohesive look in bed or sofa. Overall, the Horizon collection, with its fine play of colours and advanced pattern, is a result of the particularly refined craftsmanship in Peru and therefore encapsulates Elvang's DNA to a great extent. Horizon is woven from a blend of recycled sheep and alpaca wool, and this special combination of fibres makes it light, durable and soft at the same time. The recycled wool is processed at our local supplier in Peru, which means that the wool comes from other productions and would otherwise be considered waste. By pulling the wool apart, the original fibres emerge and new yarn can be spun and woven into new textiles. In this way, Elvang helps to utilise already existing resources that, instead of being discarded, are given new life with us.Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the throw is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.In general, there is no need to wash or dry clean wool as the material has self-cleaning properties and the fibres themselves have a unique structure that repels odours and dirt. The natural grease in the wool also helps to protect the material because it forms a film that prevents bacteria, for example, from penetrating, making frequent washing or cleaning unnecessary. If your throw does need to be cleaned, we recommend dry cleaning, which will keep its beautiful surface unchanged for as long as possible.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% other fiber
Weight: app. 560 gram
Size: 130x200 cm / 51x79 inche
Care: Dry clean only

products.name: Elvang Manhattan Cushion/Terracotta/red magma / 50x50cm
products.description:
The Manhattan cushion is inspired by the way the straight streets and right angles create square blocks in New York’s borough of Manhattan. Lines crisscross and create contrast and vibrancy. The design creates a balance between the classic, timeless and forward-thinking modern look.The Manhattan cushion is woven from 100% recycled materials.The cushion is made from the amazingly soft recycled alpaca & sheep wool. Weaving textiles of alpaca fibres is a Peruvian tradition that can be traced back to the Inca times. Alpaca fibres are soft, durable and offer more warmth than other natural fibres. Pilling is at an absolute minimum and the cushion will maintain a fresh and new look for a long time. The cushion is made of 100% sustainable fibres. Elvang is fair trade certified at the highest possible level within the World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO) as Guaranteed Member. This guarantees that the cushion is woven under responsible conditions for both the environment, humans and animals.

Material: 50% alpaca wool, 40% sheep wool & 10% andre fiber
Weight: app. 190 gram
Size: 50x50 cm / 20x20 inches
Care: Dry clean only
